01/24/84  gcos_create_file, gcf

Syntax:  gcf filename {-control_arg}


Function:  creates a segment or MSF to be used as a GCOS file.


Arguments:
filename
   is the Multics pathname of the file to be created.


Control arguments:
-llinks n
   specifies the file size in llinks (1 llink = 320 words)
-links n
   specifies the file size in links (1 link = 12 llinks)


Notes: If no file size specification is given the file will be created
with a size of 1 llink.
